<item>
            <title>[SPR-6335] Assert should use MessageFormat to avoid building unecessary Strings as error message</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/SPR-6335</link>
                <project id="10000" key="SPR">Spring Framework</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;log4j users used to wrapp debug code with isDebugEnabled to avoid building logging Strings and calling toString() when not necessary. slf4j Uses MessageFormat as a workaround :&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;logger.debug( &quot;some log about {}&quot;, object );&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Spring Assert also is supposed to only fire an exception when some unexpected error occurs. Using same strategy it could avoid building the error message anytime an assertion is checked :&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;// Many String concatenation + implicit toString() calls&lt;br/&gt;
Assert.notNull( &quot;the entity &quot; + entity + &quot; with ID &quot; + id + &quot; is not of type &quot; + type );&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;// Less useless CPU consumed in happy path&lt;br/&gt;
Assert.notNull( &quot;the entity {} with ID {} is not of type {}&quot;, entity, id, type );&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;using varags can also make the parameter list as long as necessary for assertion message to contain all contextual elements the developper may provide.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
